   "source": [
    "# Movie Recommender System (Content-Based)\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates a content-based movie recommender system using TF-IDF vectorization and cosine similarity on movie metadata.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Features:**\n",
    "- Cleans and processes movie data\n",
    "- Extracts features using TF-IDF on combined tags\n",
    "- Computes similarity between movies\n",
    "- Provides a `recommend()` function to get similar movies\n",
    "- Saves model artifacts for deployment\n",
    "- Includes test cases for popular movies\n",
    "\n",
    "## How to Use\n",
    "1. Run all cells in order to build the model and test recommendations.\n",
    "2. Use the `recommend('movie title')` function to get recommendations for any movie in the dataset.\n",
    "3. Artifacts (`tfidf_vectorizer.pkl`, `cosine_sim.pkl`, `indices.pkl`) are saved for use in deployment/web apps.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "959259aa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Shape  : (3146, 15)\n",
      "Columns: ['id', 'title', 'overview', 'tagline', 'genres', 'keywords', 'cast', 'director', 'vote_average', 'vote_count', 'popularity', 'release_year', 'runtime', 'original_language', 'tags']\n",
      "\n",
      "Sample tags:\n",
      "🎬 avatar\n",
